<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-052-116 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 415 251</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Sept 30 1991* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Able Telecom buys Mexican firm, then sells it. (systems integratorbuys Communicaciones Digitales, S.A., sells it in merger withCommunications International)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Blankenhorn, Dana.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Able Telcom Holding Corp. (Acquisitions, mergers, divestments)Communications International (Atlanta, GA) (Acquisitions, mergers,divestments)Communicaciones Digitales SA (Acquisitions, mergers, divestments).andO;Topic:     Computer systems integratorsBusiness PlanningAcquisitionMerger.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Able Telcom Buys Mexican Firm, Then Sells It 09/30/91 DEERFIELD BEACH,FLORIDA, U.S.A, 1991 SEP 30 (NB) -- Able Telcom Holding, a smallcommunications systems integrator, bought the assets of a small Mexican phonecompany, then announced it will sell it to an Atlanta firm.andM;Able said was in final negotiations to buy the assets of ComunicacionesDigitales, S.A., of Mexico City, for cash and preferred shares with acombined value of approximately $3 million.andP;  This would bring Able a primeplace in the booming Mexican market, where work is plentiful and businessesare suddenly flush with cash, anticipating a free-trade agreement with theU.S.andP;  The company sells, installs, and services telephones andtelecommunications equipment to commercial customers throughout Mexico, andhas an $8 million contract to furnish data communications to the nationallottery.andM;Just days after that announcement, Able signed a letter of intent to mergewith Communications International, a systems integrator in Atlanta, throughan exchange of stock.andP;  CII, headed by Essie Bakhtiar, sells and servicesautomated calling devices, microwave systems, radar, voice mail, andteleconferencing systems.andP;  CII is also listed as a minority businessenterprise, participating in SBA Section 8a program, the Department ofDefense Minority Set- aside Program and others.andP;  Mr. Bakhtiar, when contactedby Newsbytes, was unaware of Able's Mexican acquisition.andP;  CII had 1990revenues of $21 million, with a $121 million backlog.andM;(Dana Blankenhorn/19910930/Press Contact: CII, Essie Bakhtiar, 404-662-8133)</TEXT></DOC>